# # const ETH_P_IP: u16 = 0x0800;
# const ETH_HDR_LEN: usize = mem::size_of::<ethhdr>(); This function will ensure that before we access any data, we check that it's contained between data and data_end. It is marked as unsafe because when calling the function, you must ensure that there is a valid T at that location or there will be undefined behaviour.

